\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. F. thymifolia} (L.) Spach ex Webb,{\i  Iter Hisp.} 69 (1838) ({\i F. viscida} Spach, {\i F. glutinosa }(L.) Boiss., {\i Helianthemum viride }Ten.). Up to 20 cm; stems erect or ascending. Leaves 5-11 × 0·5-1 mm, opposite at least below, linear, linear-lanceolate or narrowly elliptical, obtuse or mucronate, glabrous, pubescent or glandular-pubescent, with strongly revolute margins, stipulate, with small, leafy, axillary shoots. Inflorescence 3- to 9-flowered; pedicels much longer than the subtending bracts. Capsule (4-)6-seeded. 2n = 32. {\i Mediterranean region; Portugal}. Al Bl Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
