\pard\f0\fs28  A variable and puzzling species showing similarities to {\b 2}, {\b 3} and {\b 4}, possibly the result of former hybridization. Characterized among other features by the fact that from {\b 12} ovules only 6 seeds usually develop which (unlike other species) occupy the space left by the abortive ovules and fill the loculi.
