\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. R. vermiculata} L.,{\i  Syst. Nat.} ed. 10,{\b  2}: 1081 (1759) ({\i R. mucronata} Jaub. & Spach). Glabrous shrub c. 30 cm, with erect branches. Leaves up to 12 mm, semi-cylindrical, mucronate, glaucous, crowded near the base of the branch, widely spaced above, often subtending leafy, axillary short shoots. Flowers subtended by numerous imbricate bracts, which conceal the calyx. Petals c. 7 mm, white; appendages fimbriate. Stamens in 5 bundles of c. 15. Capsule globose.{\i  Banks near the sea, on gypsaceous clay. S. coast of Sicilia} ({\i Porto Empedocle}). *Si. ({\i N. Africa}.)
